body:
<!-- Please only use this template for submitting reports about failing tests in Kubernetes CI jobs -->

**Which jobs are failing**:
kubernetes/node-problem-detector/node-problem-detector-ci: ci-npd-e2e-node
See the [Prow config](https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/blob/c08ecc49e1939e90f0aefad4dcab87e5fd5f0fa5/config/jobs/kubernetes/node-problem-detector/node-problem-detector-ci.yaml#L57)

**Which test(s) are failing**:
[k8s.io] NodeProblemDetector [NodeFeature:NodeProblemDetector] [k8s.io] SystemLogMonitor should generate node condition and events for corresponding errors

**Since when has it been failing**:
Dec 03. [Last green test](https://prow.k8s.io/view/gcs/kubernetes-jenkins/logs/ci-npd-e2e-node/1202072191361880066) was at 19:50 PST, [first red test](https://prow.k8s.io/view/gcs/kubernetes-jenkins/logs/ci-npd-e2e-node/1202102643455954945) was at 21:51 PST.

**Testgrid link**:
https://k8s-testgrid.appspot.com/sig-node-node-problem-detector#ci-npd-e2e-node

**Reason for failure**:

```
• Failure in Spec Setup (BeforeEach) [0.160 seconds]
[k8s.io] NodeProblemDetector [NodeFeature:NodeProblemDetector]
/home/prow/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/_output/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e/framework/framework.go:716
  [k8s.io] SystemLogMonitor
  /home/prow/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/_output/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e/framework/framework.go:716
    should generate node condition and events for corresponding errors [BeforeEach]
    _output/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e_node/node_problem_detector_linux.go:246
    Refusing to compare <nil> to <nil>.
      
    Be explicit and use BeNil() instead.  This is to avoid mistakes where both sides of an assertion are erroneously uninitialized.
    _output/local/go/src/k8s.io/kubernetes/test/e2e_node/node_problem_detector_linux.go:107
```
Apparently [this](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/d9ed6110e88e73da597cc03a38ee1357f9b67ed3/test/e2e_node/node_problem_detector_linux.go#L107) is the culprit.

**Anything else we need to know**:

This is likely caused by some library upgrade. Nothing big.
